  "instructions": [
    "Cook the farfalle pasta according to package instructions until al dente.",
    "Prepare the tajine vessel by heating it over low heat with a small amount of olive oil.",
    "Add the chopped olives, parsley, and dill to the heated tajine and sauté for 2-3 minutes until fragrant.",
    "Add the cherry tomatoes, white wine vinegar, dried oregano, salt, and black pepper to the tajine and stir to combine.",
    "Add the cooked farfalle pasta to the tajine and toss with the sauce until well coated.",
    "Transfer the pasta to a serving dish and top with crumbled feta cheese.",
    "Serve warm and enjoy!",
    "Store any leftovers in an airtight container for up to 3 days in the refrigerator or 2 months in the freezer."
